<TITLE> Fake army, ACC men arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 3 (bdnews24.com) - RAB Friday arrested three men who allegedly used to extort money from former lawmakers and businessmen passing themselves for members of the Bangladesh Army and the Anticorruption Commission. They are Aminul Islam, 33, Shajahan Kabir Shiplu,28, and Ahsan Habib, 30. Islam used to introduce himself as lieutenant colonel Humayun Kabir who is a member of the anticorruption taskforce. The team after a long investigation arrested the men in front of the Radisson Water Garden Hotel. They also recovered over Tk 3.97 lakh from them. RAB squadron leader Mohammad Fazal told bdnews24.com that the men had long been cheating government officials, former lawmakers and businessmen. They were being questioned, he said. bdnews
